---
// This page IS your Astro docs site — rendering real Kumo components.
// No React. No design tokens copied by hand. No inline style hacks.
// Every class on every control below is emitted by the published package.
import { Button, Badge, Field, Input } from '@acoyfellow/kumo-svelte';
import Docs from '../layouts/Docs.astro';
---

<Docs title="Kumo + Astro — native components in your docs" active="svelte">
  <p class="eyebrow">Proof of concept</p>
  <h1 class="title">Your Astro docs, using real Kumo components.</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Every interactive control below is the actual <code>@acoyfellow/kumo-svelte</code>
    component, rendered by Astro and hydrated in the browser — not a React port and
    not a hand-approximated copy of Kumo's tokens. Nothing here is styled by hand:
    every class you inspect comes straight from the package. The styling you see is
    Kumo's own — exactly what the package emits, in full color.
  </p>

  <h2 class="section">Buttons — real per-variant colors</h2>
  <p class="section-sub">
    The <code>variant</code> prop maps to real Kumo color classes emitted by the
    package. Open devtools: every class is genuine Kumo, no inline styles.
  </p>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="demo-row" data-test="buttons">
      <Button client:load variant="primary">Get started</Button>
      <Button client:load variant="secondary">View source</Button>
      <Button client:load variant="danger">Delete</Button>
      <Button client:load variant="outline">Outline</Button>
      <Button client:load variant="ghost">Ghost</Button>
    </div>
    <p class="caption">
      <code>primary</code> renders <code>bg-kumo-brand</code> (brand blue),
      <code>danger</code> renders <code>bg-kumo-danger</code> (red),
      <code>secondary</code> the neutral base control, plus <code>outline</code> and
      <code>ghost</code> — all sourced straight from Kumo's own <code>buttonVariants</code>.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 class="section">Badges — real per-variant colors</h2>
  <p class="section-sub">
    The Kumo <code>Badge</code> component maps its <code>variant</code> prop to real
    color classes — green, red, blue, amber, purple — straight from the package.
  </p>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="demo-row" data-test="badges">
      <Badge client:load variant="success">Stable</Badge>
      <Badge client:load variant="error">Deprecated</Badge>
      <Badge client:load variant="info">New</Badge>
      <Badge client:load variant="warning">Beta</Badge>
      <Badge client:load variant="purple">Experimental</Badge>
    </div>
    <p class="caption">
      Each badge renders its own real color: <code>success</code> →
      <code>bg-kumo-success-tint</code>, <code>error</code> →
      <code>bg-kumo-danger-tint</code>, <code>info</code> →
      <code>bg-kumo-info-tint</code>, and so on — exactly what the package emits,
      no inline styles, no hand-copied tokens.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 class="section">Forms work too</h2>
  <p class="section-sub">
    Kumo's <code>Field</code> and <code>Input</code> render server-side and hydrate cleanly
    via <code>client:load</code>. No special handling needed on the Svelte path.
  </p>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="demo-stack">
      <Field
        client:load
        id="email"
        label="Work email"
        description="We'll only use this for release notes."
        required
      />
      <Input client:load placeholder="Search the docs…" />
      <div>
        <Button client:load variant="primary">Subscribe</Button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 class="section">Why this matters</h2>
  <p class="section-sub">
    The old path forced docs authors to re-approximate Kumo's look by hand because
    Kumo only shipped React. This repo shows the clean path: consume Kumo's published
    framework components <em>directly</em> from a plain Astro site — full color, the
    real package styling, with zero hand-styling.
  </p>

  <h2 class="section">Install &amp; use — the whole recipe</h2>
  <p class="section-sub">Five lines. This is the entire integration.</p>
  <pre><code>{`npm i @acoyfellow/kumo-svelte
// astro.config.mjs -> integrations: [svelte()]

import { Button, Badge, Field, Input } from '@acoyfellow/kumo-svelte';
import '@acoyfellow/kumo-svelte/styles.css';
// then: <Button client:load variant="primary">Get started</Button>`}</code></pre>

  <div class="note">
    <strong>How to read this page:</strong> the surrounding chrome (sidebar, header) is
    plain HTML/CSS so the proof is unambiguous — anything that looks like a UI control
    here is a genuine Kumo component, with zero inline styling and zero hand-copied
    tokens. Buttons and badges render their real per-variant colors straight from the
    package. The <a href="/vue">Vue path</a> works the same way — clean SSR + hydrate.
  </div>
</Docs>
